<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="160" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,775,1422]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,775,800]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Metope wide, almost square, with distinct median and sublateral carinae joined at one point on its upper margin which is straight (
<figureCitation box="[446,514,812,837]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,749,1969]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,736,1978]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Thionia cinctifrons (Stål), holotype. 1—frontal view; 2—dorsal view; 3—lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1290886/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Metope and coryphe joined at obtuse angle (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[1246,1316,812,837]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,749,1969]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,736,1978]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Thionia cinctifrons (Stål), holotype. 1—frontal view; 2—dorsal view; 3—lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1290886/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Coryphe transverse (
<figureCitation box="[281,351,847,872]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,749,1969]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,736,1978]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Thionia cinctifrons (Stål), holotype. 1—frontal view; 2—dorsal view; 3—lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1290886/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Fore wings long and narrow, rounded apically, far surpassing the apex of abdomen. Forewing vein sequence: R 2–3, with first furcation near to basal cell; M 2, furcating before wing middle; CuΑ 1. Clavus long, open –Pcu+Α1 runs into apex of clavus. Hind wings well developped, 3-lobed. Hindwing vein sequence: R 2, furcating after wing middle; M 1; CuΑ 2, furacting apically; CuP 1; Pcu 2, furcating apically and partly fused with Α1.1 at mid length; Α1 2; Α2 2, furcating at mid length (
<figureCitation box="[748,817,994,1019]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,749,1969]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,736,1978]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Thionia cinctifrons (Stål), holotype. 1—frontal view; 2—dorsal view; 3—lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1290886/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,775,1422]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1037,1062]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Notes.</emphasis>
Thanks to kind help of Dr. Gunvi Lindberg the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1854" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1854" box="[1017,1321,1037,1062]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Issus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinctifrons">
<emphasis box="[1017,1200,1038,1062]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Issus cinctifrons</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1207,1321,1037,1062]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" refId="ref6656" refString="Stal, C. (1854) Nya Hemiptera. Ofversigt af Kongliga Svenska Fetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar. Stockholm, 11, 231 - 255." type="journal article">Stål, 1854</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is located in the collection of Naturhistoriska Riksmuseet in Stockholm (Sweden). This single male perfectly matching with Stål’s original description of the species (
<bibRefCitation box="[609,776,1109,1134]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" refId="ref6656" refString="Stal, C. (1854) Nya Hemiptera. Ofversigt af Kongliga Svenska Fetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar. Stockholm, 11, 231 - 255." type="journal article">Stål 1854: 247</bibRefCitation>
). In particular 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1854" box="[938,1079,1110,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Issus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinctifrons">
<emphasis box="[938,1079,1110,1134]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">I. cinctifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by wide almost square metope with median carina running from its upper margin to its middle and full sublateral carinae turned to median line above clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[476,545,1181,1206]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,749,1969]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,736,1978]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Thionia cinctifrons (Stål), holotype. 1—frontal view; 2—dorsal view; 3—lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1290886/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Metope with two rows of yellow spots—traces of larval sensory pits. Fore wings long and narrow, light brown yellowish with green spots besides of claval suture and with longitudinal veins yellow greenish (
<figureCitation box="[342,442,1253,1278]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,749,1969]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,736,1978]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Thionia cinctifrons (Stål), holotype. 1—frontal view; 2—dorsal view; 3—lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1290886/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Figs 2, 3</figureCitation>
). From other side according to Spinola’s description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1839" box="[1060,1278,1253,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Issus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrocostatus">
<emphasis box="[1060,1278,1253,1278]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Issus rubrocostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this species is characterized by metope much longer than wide, without carinae—“Front, plus long que large…sans traces de divisions en trois facettes…” and “Base du front…sans arête médiane.” (
<bibRefCitation box="[1014,1235,1325,1350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" refId="ref6618" refString="Spinola, M. (1839) Sur les Fulgorelles, sous-tribu de la tribu des Cicadaires, ordre des Rhyngotes. Suite. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 8, 339 - 454." type="journal article">Spinola 1839: 357</bibRefCitation>
). In coloration 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1839" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Issus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrocostatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">I. rubrocostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by red longitudinal veins of fore wings—“Nervures principales, rouges…” (
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="160" refId="ref6618" refString="Spinola, M. (1839) Sur les Fulgorelles, sous-tribu de la tribu des Cicadaires, ordre des Rhyngotes. Suite. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 8, 339 - 454." type="journal article">Spinola 1839</bibRefCitation>
). Thus it is clear that M. Spinola and C. Stål described two different species from Brazil.
</paragraph>
